[4]
Date: Fri 10 Jan 2003
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@derwent.co.uk>
Source: Winnipeg Sun online, Fri 10 Jan 2003 [edited]
<http://www.canoe.ca/WinnipegNews/ws.ws-01-10-0014.html>

Canada: suspected norovirus outbreak at seniors complex in Winnipeg
-------------------------------------------------------
A possible outbreak of norovirus infection affected a Winnipeg seniors
complex in Winnipeg last week. Between 15 and 20 residents on a community
living ward at the core-area seniors center suddenly fell ill last
Thursday. A couple of staff members also got sick. Although it wasn't
confirmed as a gastrointestinal outbreak, Devlin said symptoms were similar
to those associated with norovirus infection.
According to Manitoba Health, the province has experienced 46
gastrointestinal outbreaks since 1 November 2002 -- including 29 in
personal care homes and 4 in elderly housing complexes. 10 hospitals and
one school also reported possible cases of the virus.
Workers at Lions Centre restricted contact between residents, and staff
increased housekeeping and disinfecting procedures and "washed their hands
lots," Devlin said. Residents and staff have since returned to good health.
